genresAdvancedInfo.name: cantonese worship
genresAdvancedInfo.description: This genre is a form of religious music that originated in Hong Kong and is sung in the Cantonese dialect. It features uplifting and inspirational lyrics that are meant to praise and worship God. Cantonese worship music is often accompanied by traditional Chinese instruments such as the erhu and guzheng, as well as modern instruments like the guitar and keyboard.
